description.narrative: While in the second year of COVID-19 pandemic and amid sustained volatility in the socio-political environment, opportunities for public communication work continued to be limited, happening largely online. The total reach of media and social media publications mentioning UNICEF and programming was over 10 million views in 2021. Dominant subjects for public communication activities were COVID-19 and disability, as well as the migrant situation at the Belarus-Poland border and UNICEF 75 anniversary in the second half of the year. Communication messages focused on the results of our work for the most vulnerable children, reflecting neutrality and impartiality. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/01/2022
